{"id":2,"parent_id":0,"book_id":44,"content_id":1,"language_id":1,"display_order":2,"title":"Lesson 1: Introduction to the Doctrine and Covenants and Church History","subtitle":"","short_title":"Lesson 1","uri":"/manual/doctrine-and-covenants-and-church-history-class-member-study-guide/lesson-1-introduction-to-the-doctrine-and-covenants-and-church-history","content":[["div",{"id":"head1","uri":"/manual/doctrine-and-covenants-and-church-history-class-member-study-guide/lesson-1-introduction-to-the-doctrine-and-covenants-and-church-history.head1"},[".titleNumber","Lesson",["span.dominant","1"]],["h1","Introduction to the Doctrine and Covenants and Church History"],[".kicker","Reading assignment: Explanatory Introduction to the Doctrine and Covenants;",["a.scriptureRef",{"href":"/scriptures/dc-testament/dc/1"},"Doctrine and Covenants 1"],";",["a.crossRef",{"href":"/manual/our-heritage-a-brief-history-of-the-church-of-jesus-christ-of-latter-day-saints/introduction.p1"},"introduction"],"to",["span.emphasis","Our Heritage."]]],[".bodyBlock",["ul.bullet",["li",["span.label","•"],[".para","How is the Doctrine and Covenants different from other books of scripture? (See the third paragraph in the Explanatory Introduction.)"]]],["div",{"id":"p5","uri":"/manual/doctrine-and-covenants-and-church-history-class-member-study-guide/lesson-1-introduction-to-the-doctrine-and-covenants-and-church-history.p5"},"On 1 November 1831, the Prophet Joseph Smith presided at a special conference of elders, held in Hiram, Ohio. Those in attendance decided to compile some of the revelations the Prophet had received and publish them in a book called the Book of Commandments. Following the first session of this conference, the Lord signified His approval for the publication by giving Joseph Smith a revelation that He called “my preface unto the book of my commandments” (",["a.scriptureRef",{"href":"/scriptures/dc-testament/dc/1.6"},"D&C 1:6"],"). This revelation is now section 1 of the Doctrine and Covenants."],["ul.bullet",["li",["span.label","•"],[".para","What warnings does the Lord issue in",["a.scriptureRef",{"href":"/scriptures/dc-testament/dc/1"},"D&C 1"],"? (See verses",["a.scriptureRef",{"href":"/scriptures/dc-testament/dc/1.7-10,12-16,31-33"},"D&C 1:7–10, 12–16, 31–33"],".)"]],["li",["span.label","•"],[".para","What are some of the purposes of the revelations in the Doctrine and Covenants? (See",["a.scriptureRef",{"href":"/scriptures/dc-testament/dc/1.17-28"},"D&C 1:17–28"],".)"]]],["div",{"id":"p8","uri":"/manual/doctrine-and-covenants-and-church-history-class-member-study-guide/lesson-1-introduction-to-the-doctrine-and-covenants-and-church-history.p8"},"This dispensation can be divided into six historical periods, each of which will be discussed in this year’s course:"],["div",{"id":"f3","uri":"/manual/doctrine-and-covenants-and-church-history-class-member-study-guide/lesson-1-introduction-to-the-doctrine-and-covenants-and-church-history.f3"},["table",["tbody",["tr",["td",{"colspan":"1","rowspan":"1"},[".para","New York Period"]],["td",{"colspan":"1","rowspan":"1"},[".para","1820–1830"]]],["tr",["td",{"colspan":"1","rowspan":"1"},[".para","Ohio-Missouri Period"]],["td",{"colspan":"1","rowspan":"1"},[".para","1831–1838"]]],["tr",["td",{"colspan":"1","rowspan":"1"},[".para","Nauvoo Period"]],["td",{"colspan":"1","rowspan":"1"},[".para","1839–1846"]]],["tr",["td",{"colspan":"1","rowspan":"1"},[".para","Pioneering the West"]],["td",{"colspan":"1","rowspan":"1"},[".para","1846–1898"]]],["tr",["td",{"colspan":"1","rowspan":"1"},[".para","Expansion of the Church"]],["td",{"colspan":"1","rowspan":"1"},[".para","1899–1950"]]],["tr",["td",{"colspan":"1","rowspan":"1"},[".para","The Worldwide Church"]],["td",{"colspan":"1","rowspan":"1"},[".para","1951–present"]]]]]],[".topic",["h2","Scripture Chain: The Lord’s Word in the Doctrine and Covenants"],["ul.noMarker",["li",[".para",["a.scriptureRef",{"href":"/scriptures/dc-testament/dc/1.37-39"},"D&C 1:37–39"]]],